 ), and VISIT (Vegetation Integrated Simulator for Trace gases) (
 
  62
 ). Three TRENDY model experiments were used to evaluate the relative contribution of atmospheric CO
 2 concentration and climate change to GPP: (S0) no forcing change, (S1) varying CO
 2 only, and (S2) varying CO
 2 and climate. The model differences of S1 and S0 and 
 Eq. 20 were used to estimate GPP sensitivities to atmospheric CO
 2 concentration, and the differences of S2 and S1 and 
 Eq. 22 were used to estimate GPP sensitivities to three climate variables: air temperature (β
 Ta), VPD (β
 VPD), and PAR (β
 PAR).
